#
# WHY pulldown-cmark IS THE 74TH RUST CLI LIBRARY
#
# pulldown-cmark is the canonical Rust CommonMark parser.
# Distinct from all previously-documented Rust libraries in
# this taxonomy by being a MARKDOWN PARSER — a fundamentally
# new abstraction (none of logging, errors, tables, progress,
# colors, prompts, boxes, humanization, text wrap, config,
# paths, dates, HTTP, file watching, or WebSockets concerns).
#
# Five distinguishing characteristics:
#
#   1. COMMONMARK 0.31 COMPLIANT — pulldown-cmark passes the
#      full CommonMark 0.31 specification's >650-test
#      conformance suite.  Distinct from comrak (more GFM-
#      focused, slower for pure CommonMark) and markdown-rs
#      (incomplete coverage).
#
#   2. EVENT-BASED PULL PARSER — emits an Iterator of `Event`
#      values; minimizes memory by never allocating a full AST.
#      Pull-parsing model (caller advances the iterator,
#      processes one event, repeats) vs. push-parsing (callbacks)
#      vs. DOM-parsing (full tree).  Pull is the most memory-
#      efficient of the three for streaming Markdown.
#
#   3. ~200x FASTER THAN markdown.js — pulldown-cmark benchmarks
#      among the fastest CommonMark implementations across all
#      languages.  Zero-copy string handling + iterator model
#      eliminates intermediate allocations.
#
#   4. OPTIONAL GFM EXTENSIONS via Options bitflags — caller
#      explicitly opts into tables, footnotes, strikethrough,
#      task lists, heading attributes, smart punctuation.
#      Distinct from comrak (always-on GFM) and markdown-it
#      (plugin-based extensions).
#
#   5. RAPH-LEVIEN / PULLDOWN-CMARK-RS / RUSTDOC-LINEAGE
#      ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — distinct from Sean McArthur
#      (Hyperium), Tolnay (serde), Sorhus (Node CLI),
#      Mockers (notify-rs), Abramov (snapview), Pinca
#      (websockets), Ronacher (console-rs).  Raph Levien
#      brings graphics-engineering perspective to Rust
#      text processing.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# THE mdzk CLI — clap derive + pulldown-cmark + jql + gray_matter
#
# mdzk's CLI is in src/main.rs.  Uses clap v4 derive with a
# single root command (no subcommands).
#
# Source:
#     #[derive(Parser)]
#     #[clap(version, about)]
#     struct Mdzk {
#         #[clap(default_value = ".", hide_default_value = true)]
#         /// JSON querying string
#         query: String,
#
#         #[clap(short, long, default_value = "3", value_name = "LEVEL", global = true)]
#         /// The logging level of mdzk
#         log_level: usize,
#
#         #[clap(short, long, default_value = ".", value_name = "DIR",
#                hide_default_value = true, global = true)]
#         /// Path to a vault source
#         source: PathBuf,
#
#         #[clap(short, long, action = clap::ArgAction::Append)]
#         /// List of gitignore patterns for the directory walker
#         ignore: Vec<String>,
#
#         #[clap(long)]
#         /// Prettify the JSON output
#         pretty: bool,
#
#         #[clap(short, long)]
#         /// Output shell-compatible raw strings and arrays
#         raw: bool,
#     }
#
# Flags:
#   -l, --log-level LEVEL   logging level 1-5 (default 3 = info)
#   -s, --source DIR        path to vault source directory
#                           (default current dir)
#   -i, --ignore PATTERN    gitignore-style exclusion pattern
#                           (repeatable)
#       --pretty            prettify JSON output
#   -r, --raw               output shell-compatible raw strings
#                           and arrays
#   -h, --help              show help
#   -V, --version           show version
#
# Positional:
#   QUERY                   jql query string (default "." = full vault)
#
# pulldown-cmark is used in src/note/ for parsing each .md file
# into a structured note representation with extracted backlinks,
# tags, and metadata.
#
# Five-axis distinctness from all previously-documented Rust
# libraries:
#
#   1. MARKDOWN I/O ABSTRACTION — pulldown-cmark parses
#      Markdown; distinct from every other Axis.
#
#   2. EVENT-BASED PULL PARSER — vs DOM parsers (comrak) and
#      push parsers (callbacks).
#
#   3. ~200x FASTER THAN markdown.js — pure-Rust performance.
#
#   4. CommonMark 0.31 + opt-in GFM via Options bitflags.
#
#   5. RAPH-LEVIEN / PULLDOWN-CMARK-RS / GRAPHICS-ENGINEERING
#      ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — distinct maintainer lineage.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# COMMAND-LINE OPTIONS (sourced directly from
# https://github.com/mdzk-rs/mdzk/blob/main/src/main.rs
# clap v4 derive #[clap] attributes.)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
typeset -A opt_args

local -a _mdzk_log_levels
_mdzk_log_levels=(
    '1:error level'
    '2:warn level'
    '3:info level (default)'
    '4:debug level'
    '5:trace level'
)

_arguments -s -S \
    '(-l --log-level)'{-l+,--log-level=}'[logging level (1-5)]:level:->log_level' \
    '(-s --source)'{-s+,--source=}'[path to vault source directory]:directory:_files -/' \
    '*'{-i+,--ignore=}'[gitignore-style exclusion pattern]:pattern:_default' \
    '--pretty[prettify JSON output]' \
    '(-r --raw)'{-r,--raw}'[output shell-compatible raw strings and arrays]' \
    '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
    '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
    '*:jql query:_default' \
    && ret=0

case $state in
    log_level)
        _describe -t levels 'log level' _mdzk_log_levels && ret=0
        ;;
esac

return ret
